Package: abis
Version: @VERSION@
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: mattiIce <noreply@users.noreply.github.com>
Section: web
Priority: optional
Depends: adduser, tzdata, libc6, libstdc++6, libicu74 | libicu72 | libicu71 | libicu70 | libicu67 | libicu66
Recommends: nginx, certbot, python3-certbot-nginx
Homepage: https://github.com/mattiIce/ABIS
Description: ABIS API and web UIs (native systemd service)
 Modernized order/coil/job system: an ASP.NET Core API plus the greenfield web
 screens it serves, running as a hardened systemd service next to the plant
 Oracle database. The .NET runtime is bundled (self-contained), so no runtime
 needs to be installed separately.
 .
 After install, run `sudo abis-configure` to set the Oracle connection string,
 the API key, and an optional nginx + TLS (Let's Encrypt) front, then start the
 service. See /usr/share/doc/abis/.
